        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 1:50PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 149 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Carson City Airport, or near Carson City, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carson City, Washoe City, Pleasant Valley, Carson City Airport, New
Washoe City, Indian Hills, Washoe Lake Campground, Us 395 At
Douglas-Carson City Co Line, Lakeview, Gold Hill, Davis Creek
Campground, Stewart, Us 50 At Carson City-Lyon Co Line, and Junction
U.S 50 And NV 341.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
